-3. Request Line -> A server that receives a request-target onger than any URI it wishes to parse MUST respond with a 414
-3.2 A server MUST respond with a 400 status code to any HTTP/1.1 request message that lacks a Host header field
-3.3 Reconstructing the Target URI (maybe after the parsing)
-5.1 Field Line Parsing -> Parse content of every field line (not necessary)
-5.2 Handle obsolete line folding
-6.1 Transfer Encoding -> A server that receives a request message with a transfer coding it does not understand should respond with 501
-6.1 -> A server or client that receives an HTTP/1.0 message containing a Transfer-Encoding field MUST treat the message
-6.3 -> 5. If a message is received with an invalid Content-Length then the message must treat as an unrecoverable error and respond with a 400 ...
-6.3 -> 6. If the sender closes the connection the server must consider the message to be incomplete and close the connection
-8. -> Check if the zero-sized chunk has been received or if the message body received is equal to the content-length

